01/05/2011
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- European Commission (EC) Director for the Western Balkans Pierre Mirel says he is impressed by judicial reforms Montenegro has implemented over the past four months. 
During a meeting Friday (April 29th) in Podgorica with Justice Minister Dusko Markovic, Mirel also praised the broad dialogue among the government, the parliament and the civil society on the topic. 
Markovic briefed the EU official on efforts to implement such reforms and to fight organised crime and corruption. 
(RTCG, Radio Free Europe - 29/04/11)
